  "special": {
    "title": "Good for starting fires.",
    "description": "Fires slow arcing rounds that explode on contact for splash damage, and that splash scales with grenade damage bonuses. It is always incendiary, uses 2 ammo per shot, and trades direct bullet damage for stronger elemental pressure."
  },
  "notes": "While A Train to Catch is active, shooting the snowman's head in southern Tundra Express near the vending machines makes a Tinderbox drop. After you pick it up or finish the mission, it will not appear there again. That one-off drop acts as a safety net so players are likely to get a fire weapon early, which Roland explicitly hints at. It also appears as a mission weapon in Clan War: Trailer Trashing, but you do not need it to complete the objective. Its splash damage scales with grenade damage bonuses.",
